1. Why does the following expression 0.1 + 0.2 === 0.3 evaluate to false in Javascript?
    Because float numbers cannot be stored accurately in decimal. The computer uses binary to store information.
2. What does the method attribute on a form element decide?
    The method attribute specifies how to send form-data. It can be sent as URL variables or as HTTP post transaction. 
3. Explain why the form fields appear in the URL when the method on form element is changed to GET?
    As said, because method="get" send the form-data as URL variables.
4. Why is it considered bad practice to only validate form input with HTML5 and/or Javascript?
    Because of the security aspect. Local validation does help with correction of wrong input, but the security is bad. 
    You also want to validate form input on your server.
5. When is it appropriate to use textarea over input?
    When you're expecting a longer text. Inputs like names, age and similar uses input, but questions like this one should use textareas. 
